sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst 'always' will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

forceMount.name: forceMount
forceMount.description:
Used to force mounting when more control is needed. Useful when
controlling animation with Vue animation libraries.

side.name: side
side.description:
The preferred side of the trigger to render against when open.
Will be reversed when collisions occur and avoidCollisions
is enabled.

sideOffset.name: sideOffset
sideOffset.description: The distance in pixels from the trigger.

align.name: align
align.description:
The preferred alignment against the trigger.
May change when collisions occur.

alignOffset.name: alignOffset
alignOffset.description: An offset in pixels from the `start` or `end` alignment options.

avoidCollisions.name: avoidCollisions
avoidCollisions.description:
When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

ariaLabel.name: ariaLabel
ariaLabel.description:
By default, screenreaders will announce the content inside
the component. If this is not descriptive enough, or you have
content that cannot be announced, use aria-label as a more
descriptive label.

props.name: defaultOpen
props.description:
The open state of the tooltip when it is initially rendered.
Use when you do not need to control its open state.

props.name: delayDuration
props.description:
Override the duration given to the `Provider` to customise
the open delay for a specific tooltip.

props.name: disableClosingTrigger
props.description: When `true`, clicking on trigger will not close the content.

props.name: disableHoverableContent
props.description:
Prevents Tooltip.Content from remaining open when hovering.
Disabling this has accessibility consequences. Inherits
from Tooltip.Provider.

props.name: ignoreNonKeyboardFocus
props.description:
Prevent the tooltip from opening if the focus did not come from
the keyboard by matching against the `:focus-visible` selector.
This is useful if you want to avoid opening it when switching
browser tabs or closing a dialog.

props.description: The keyboard keys to display in the tooltip.
